casebody.data:
JAMES F. BROWN, Plaintiff and Appellant, v. JOHN COMBES et al., Defendants and Respondents.

Before Freedman, Curtis, and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided June 28, 1873. Goodrich & Wheeler, for appellant. Charles Whelp, for respondent.

Opinion by Van Vorst, J. Freedman and Curtis, JJ., concurred.

Action to recover value of property shipped to a commission merchant.

Appeal from judgment for defendant.

Judgment reversed.
